{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_1","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' .claude/plans/loloop/evolution-2026-04-14-m4-spotlight-loop-exit-review.md\"","aggregated_output":"# Evolution Note — Milestone 4 Spotlight Loop Exit Review\n\n## Plan\n\n- path: `.claude/plans/active-codex-managed-agent-roadmap.md`\n- milestone: `Milestone 4 — Operational Reliability`\n- bounded target: run a spotlight loop-state exit review to decide whether this inspector-level status path is now good enough to move on to the next operational reliability gap\n\n## Completed\n\n- Reviewed the spotlight `Auto Loop` metric against the Milestone 4 goal of making loop state legible across surfaces\n- Confirmed that selected-thread inspection now shows compact loop state without requiring a return to thread rows or larger board cards\n- Determined that the next smallest operational reliability gap is explicit Codex visibility control: the roadmap calls for `Show in Codex / Hide from Codex`, but the current UI still exposes only lower-level open/archive actions\n- Narrowed the next bounded slice to an audit of the current visibility-control path\n\n## Failed or Deferred\n\n- No code changes were made in this review slice\n- No packaging run was needed because behavior did not change\n\n## Decisions\n\n- Treat the spotlight loop-state path as good enough to stop iterating for now\n- Move the next bounded slice to visibility-control auditing instead of continuing to polish inspector status chrome\n\n## Next Handoff\n\n```text\nContinue the codex-loop from `.claude/plans/active-codex-managed-agent-roadmap.md` using `ROADMAP.md` as the anchor. Stay on Milestone 4. Do one minimal slice only: audit the current visibility-control path to identify the first smallest `Show in Codex / Hide from Codex` gap, then update the active plan, append a new evolution note, and sync to `/home/clashuser/hzh/work_bo/codex_manager/vscode-extension`.\n```\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_2","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '82,114p' .claude/plans/active-codex-managed-agent-roadmap.md\"","aggregated_output":"### Milestone 4 — Operational Reliability\nStatus: active\n\nTargets:\n- background continue observability\n- clear loop status semantics\n- degraded-state handling\n- linked-vs-running distinction across surfaces\n\nAudit findings:\n- host-side auto-continue state already records `armed / queued / running / failed / success`, plus the last log path and last result detail\n- detailed loop state is currently visible inside larger board cards, but not in the compact thread-list scanning surface\n- first bounded reliability gap: users cannot quickly scan which threads have an armed, queued, running, or failed auto-loop without opening richer card UI\n\nExit review:\n- thread rows now expose compact loop state, while larger board cards still retain the richer log/result detail path\n- this is enough to satisfy the immediate loop-status scanning gap without changing host-side detached resume behavior\n- explorer grouping now gives `linked` threads a dedicated bucket instead of folding them into generic idle\n- spotlight now exposes a compact auto-loop log action, so log access is no longer confined to larger board cards\n- degraded-state recovery now exposes a direct service-log action instead of plain log-path text\n- spotlight now exposes the compact auto-loop state directly, which is sufficient for this inspector-level status gap\n- next smallest Milestone 4 gap is explicit Codex visibility control: the roadmap calls for `Show in Codex / Hide from Codex`, but current UI still only exposes lower-level open/archive actions\n\nCurrent bounded slice:\n- audit current visibility-control path to identify the first smallest `Show in Codex / Hide from Codex` gap\n\n### Milestone 5 — Publishable Product Quality\nStatus: pending\n\nTargets:\n- release workflow\n- screenshots / notes / docs\n- smoke validation routine\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
